	   <tr><td colspan=2>It all depends.  What level are we talking about?  When the high level damage bonus starts kicking in, low delay is everything, practicly.  If I was level 1, I would like the 13 delay weapon for raising skills, but I would rather have the 30/60 weapon to do damage.  If I was level 60.... OMG the 13 delay weapon would be super super good while the weapon with the slightly better ratio would do less damage in the end due to the delay.  Considering that the offhand weapons do not recieve the damage bonuses that you get at higher levels, I would probably opt for the 30/60 in your offhand with the 6/13 in your primary hand.  My primary is not a melee class but from everything I have heard, at higher levels ratio is important for the offhand and delay is a bit more important than ratio for the primary<br>&nbsp;<br>Reegor Mortees &lt;The Keepers&gt;<br>58th Defiler<br>E'Ci<br>Boo Boo is my lengthy motsa ball.</td></tr>
