	   <tr><td colspan=2>Verant has stated that Charisma has an effect on SECONDARY Saves for Charm Spells.  This means that Charisma will ONLY affect the duration of your Charm spells and the only effect it will have is to make it more likely the creature will be charmed for the duration of the spell.<br><br>Near as I can find, they never mentioned anything about Charisma affecting Mez type spells and one of the better websites states this:<br><br>[Charisma: This affects amount you will be paid for goods by NPC merchants, and how much they will pay you.  It also affects the saving throw on certain Bard and Enchanter spells (charms in particular).  There is much debate over the true importance of Charisma for enchanters.  It seems that the truly defining element which impacts on charm durations, mesmerise resists and other supposedly "charisma" based spells is actually the targets Magic Resistance.  Some people claim that it makes a large difference.  Studies run at Casters Realm have been inconclusive, so you may choose to say "better safe than sorry" and add some points at creation.]<br><br>So, take what you will from that.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>The Unnamed One<br></td></tr>
